It is a common practice when campusing to contact the rung with a slope grip and then switching to a crimp grip in order to pull off it; this way we can reach higher while doing some extra dynamic finger work. But we have to ponder whether we do it deliberately, or it is just a trick to reach longer that keeps us from focusing on the essential initial phase: exploding to get the most possible momentum.
